

Example 1: Simple Function
```
Define a function to add two numbers
add_numbers <- function(x, y) {
  result <- x + y
  return(result)
}

Call the function
result <- add_numbers(5, 10)
print(result)  # Output: 15
```

Example 2: Function with Default Argument
```
Define a function to greet someone
greet <- function(name = "World") {
  message <- paste("Hello, ", name, "!")
  return(message)
}

Call the function with default argument
print(greet())  # Output: "Hello, World!"

Call the function with custom argument
print(greet("John"))  # Output: "Hello, John!"
```

Example 3: Function with Multiple Return Values
```
Define a function to calculate mean and median
calculate_stats <- function(x) {
  mean_value <- mean(x)
  median_value <- median(x)
  return(list(mean = mean_value, median = median_value))
}

Call the function
stats <- calculate_stats(c(1, 2, 3, 4, 5))
print(stats)  # Output: $mean [1] 3 $median [1] 3
```
